Building from command line
==========================
You will need, other than g++ and associated tools: the Qt6 development tools, libraries and headers, as well as the libraries and headers for GMP.

And you will also need cmake.

Then, just run:

cmake -B build -S .
cmake --build build

This will create a directory called "build" with all the compiled files.

For some building and packaging hints, you could look at the Arch Linux PKGBUILD file.
